      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like the way you think! This was in fact my first take when I started working on this CL.\n\nThere are two reasons I ended up moving the `copy_if_needed` call back into the individual cases:\n- Most Expressions don\u0027t actually have a Type of their own, or take a Type in their constructor at all; they just get it from one of their inner Expressions. \n- By itself, calling `copy_if_needed` doesn\u0027t actually solve the issue. When constructing the cloned object, we have to actually pass `copiedType` instead of `expr.type()`. So each case still needed individual care.\n\nWhen all is said and done, this CL actually does use `copy_if_needed` in every place that expr.type() was previously used. It doesn\u0027t seem like a lot but that\u0027s because expressions with a novel Type are rare.",
